m.github.ben-manes.caffeine/caffeine/2.9.3/stats.json:9:          \\\"totalCalls\\\" : 21\\nstats/com.github.ben-manes.caffeine/caffeine/2.9.3/stats.json:12:      \\\"coverageRatio\\\" : 0.666667,\\nstats/com.github.ben-manes.caffeine/caffeine/2.9.3/stats.json:13:      \\\"coveredCalls\\\" : 14,\\nstats/com.github.ben-manes.caffeine/caffeine/2.9.3/stats.json:14:      \\\"totalCalls\\\" : 21\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_37\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"rg -n \\\\\\\"dynamicAccess|coveredCalls|totalCalls|coverageRatio|stats.json\\\\\\\" src buildSrc tck-build-logic -g '*.java' -g '*.groovy' -g '*.kt'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_37\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"rg -n \\\\\\\"dynamicAccess|coveredCalls|totalCalls|coverageRatio|stats.json\\\\\\\" src buildSrc tck-build-logic -g '*.java' -g '*.groovy' -g '*.kt'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"rg: src: No such file or directory (os error 2)\\nrg: buildSrc: No such file or directory (os error 2)\\nrg: tck-build-logic: No such file or directory (os error 2)\\n\",\"exit_code\":2,\"status\":\"failed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_38\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"rg -n \\\\\\\"metadata coverage|dynamic access|coveredCalls|totalCalls|reflection coverage\\\\\\\" -g '*.md' -g '*.txt'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_38\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"rg -n \\\\\\\"metadata coverage|dynamic access|coveredCalls|totalCalls|reflection coverage\\\\\\\" -g '*.md' -g '*.txt'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"docs/DEVELOPING.md:317:- Generate dynamic access report: `./gradlew generateDynamicAccessReport -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`\\ndocs/DEVELOPING.md:318:- Generate dynamic access coverage report: `./gradlew generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`\\ndocs/DEVELOPING.md:326:- Analyze external dynamic access: `./gradlew analyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccess --coordinates=group:artifact:version`\\nskills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\\nskills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:60:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\\nskills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:61:   - If `totalCalls` increases while `coveredCalls` stays flat or the ratio drops, ask for additional test coverage or metadata unless the uncovered calls are clearly outside the library behavior under test.\\nskills/README.md:22:It covers new-library metadata PRs, including titles like `[GenAI] Add support for com.fasterxml:classmate:1.5.1 using gpt-5.4`, and encodes the review rules already used in this repository: reject scaffold-only tests, keep test packages separate from library packages so tests do not bypass visibility boundaries, and question metadata coverage claims that are not supported by the diff.\\nskills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:55:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\\nskills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:57:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\\nskills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:59:   - If `totalCalls` increases while `coveredCalls` stays flat or the ratio drops, ask for additional test coverage or metadata unless the uncovered calls are clearly outside the library behavior under test.\\nskills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:56:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\\nskills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\\nskills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:59:   - If `totalCalls` increases while `coveredCalls` stays flat or the ratio drops, ask for additional test coverage or metadata unless the uncovered calls are clearly outside the library behavior under test.\\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:86:    Initial --> Has{has dynamic access?}\\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:111:    Load -- \\\"loaded but no dynamic access<br/>OR total_calls == 0\\\" --> Fallback\\nforge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:112:    Load -- \\\"has dynamic access\\\" --> Phase2[Enter dynamic-access phase]\\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:420:If the library has no dynamic access, the workflow falls back to the standard `basic_iterative` strategy automatically.\\nforge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md:4:Generate test for `{library}` following provided dynamic access report, by covering as many uncovered call sites as possible across all classes.\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_39\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_39\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"# Dynamic-Access Workflow Specification\\n\\n> **See also:** [Architecture](architecture.md) ·\\n> [Native metadata exploration phase](native-metadata-exploration.md) ·\\n> [Native test verification gate](native-test-verification.md) ·\\n> [Java fail-fix workflow](fix-java-run-fail.md)\\n\\n## 1. Purpose\\n\\nThe dynamic-access workflow (`workflow: dynamic_access_iterative`) generates\\na JUnit/Kotlin/Scala test suite for a target library such that every\\n**dynamic-access call site** reported by the reachability repo's coverage tool\\nis exercised at runtime. Coverage of those call sites is required before\\nreachability metadata can be generated automatically. The workflow guides the\\nLLM agent class-by-class, feeding it the still-uncovered call sites for each\\nclass until coverage is reached or the per-class budget is exhausted.\\n\\n## 2. Inputs\\n\\n| Input | Source | Required |\\n| --- | --- | --- |\\n| Maven coordinate | `--coordinates group:artifact:version` | yes |\\n| Reachability repo path | `--reachability-metadata-path` (default: parent checkout of `forge/`) | yes |\\n| Strategy name | `--strategy-name <dynamic_access_*>` | yes |\\n| Source-context types | strategy parameter `source-context-types` | yes |\\n| Per-class iteration cap | strategy parameter `max-iterations` | yes |\\n| Per-attempt test-retry cap | strategy parameter `max-class-test-iterations` | yes |\\n| Class iteration prompt | strategy `prompts[\\\"dynamic-access-iteration\\\"]` | yes |\\n| Per-class native-test verification budget | strategy parameter `max-native-test-verification-iterations` | yes (default 100) |\\n| Native-test verification batch size | strategy parameter `native-test-verification-batch-size` | no (default 5; must be >= 1) |\\n| Keep tests without DA gain | `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` | no |\\n\\n## 3. Outputs\\n\\n- One **test class file per dynamic-access report class**, located under\\n  `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/src/test/<lang>` in the reachability\\n  repo. Test class naming substitutes `$<digit>` with `Anonymous<digit>` and\\n  `$<name>` with `Inner<name>` to avoid `$` in filenames.\\n- One git commit per resolved (or partially resolved) class, on the feature\\n  branch.\\n- A final **metadata commit** produced by the standard `_finalize_successful_iteration`\\n  / `generateMetadata` step (in benchmark mode, only `generateMetadata` runs).\\n- A schema-validated metrics record under `<metrics_repo>/.../add_new_library_support.json`;\\n  by default, `<metrics_repo>` is the run worktree's `forge/` directory.\\n\\n## 4. Preconditions and Setup\\n\\nThe following preconditions are established by `add_new_library_support.main`\\n*before* the strategy's `run(...)` is called:\\n\\n1. Repository paths and GraalVM/Java environment resolved.\\n2. Feature branch `ai/add-lib-support-<group>-<artifact>-<version>` checked out.\\n3. Gradle `scaffold` task executed for the coordinate.\\n4. Gradle `populateArtifactURLs` task executed so that `index.json` carries\\n   `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, and `documentation-url` as required.\\n5. `prepare_source_contexts(...)` has downloaded and extracted the artifacts\\n   declared by the strategy's `source-context-types`. Their files become the\\n   agent's read-only context.\\n6. Scaffold commit recorded as `checkpoint_commit_hash`. Failure recovery\\n   uses `git reset --hard <checkpoint_commit_hash>`.\\n\\n## 5. State Model\\n\\nFor one strategy `run(...)` invocation:\\n\\n- `current_report` — most recent `DynamicAccessCoverageReport` (`None` triggers\\n  fallback or hard failure depending on phase).\\n- `previous_report` — prior report; used for delta computation.\\n- `exhausted_classes: set[str]` — classes that have either been resolved or\\n  hit `max-iterations` without resolution. They are not retried.\\n- `class_checkpoint` — git SHA captured before each class attempt; used to\\n  roll back failed class iterations without losing previously committed\\n  classes.\\n- `prompt_iterations` — total agent prompts sent (returned to the caller as\\n  `global_iterations`).\\n- `successful_classes` — count of classes that contributed at least one newly\\n  covered call site and whose test changes were committed.\\n\\n## 6. Workflow\\n\\nAt a glance:\\n\\n```mermaid\\nflowchart TD\\n    Setup[Setup<br/>scaffold + source context + agent] --> Initial[Initial dynamic-access report]\\n    Initial --> Has{has dynamic access?}\\n    Has -- no --> Fallback[Fallback to basic_iterative]\\n    Has -- yes --> Loop[Per-class iteration loop]\\n    Loop -- \\\"class with coverage gain\\\" --> Gate[Native test verification gate<br/>per class]\\n    Gate -- PASSED --> Loop\\n    Gate -- FAILED --> HardFail[RUN_STATUS_FAILURE<br/>reset branch]\\n    Loop --> Wrap[Phase wrap-up]\\n    Wrap --> Final[Finalization<br/>generateMetadata &rarr; exploration &rarr; codex &rarr; commit]\\n    Fallback --> End([metrics + exit])\\n    Final --> End\\n    HardFail --> End\\n```\\n\\nThe subsections below specify each box. §6.1 covers the fallback decision,\\n§6.2 the per-class loop, §6.3 mid-run report failures, §6.4 the per-class\\nnative-test verification gate, §6.5 wrap-up, and §6.6 the finalization\\norder.\\n\\n### 6.1 Phase 1 — Initial report and fallback decision\\n\\n```mermaid\\nflowchart TD\\n    Start([run begins]) --> Gen[generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport]\\n    Gen --> Load{Load JSON report}\\n    Load -- \\\"missing / gradle failed\\\" --> Fallback\\n    Load -- \\\"loaded but no dynamic access<br/>OR total_calls == 0\\\" --> Fallback\\n    Load -- \\\"has dynamic access\\\" --> Phase2[Enter dynamic-access phase]\\n\\n    Fallback[Delegate to BasicIterativeStrategy<br/>using FALLBACK_STRATEGY_NAME] --> FBOut([Return basic-iterative result])\\n    Phase2 --> P2[See section 6.2]\\n```\\n\\nThe fallback strategy is `basic_iterative_pi_gpt-5.4` (constant\\n`FALLBACK_STRATEGY_NAME` in `dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py`). The\\nfallback runs only when no usable dynamic-access guidance exists at the\\n**start** of the run; once Phase 2 begins, a missing report mid-run is a hard\\nfailure (see 6.3).\\n\\n### 6.2 Phase 2 — Per-class iteration\\n\\nThe phase loops over uncovered classes selected from the current report,\\nskipping any class in `exhausted_classes`. For each selected class, an inner\\nloop sends the agent up to `max-iterations` targeted prompts; after each\\nprompt, tests are retried up to `max-class-test-iterations` times before the\\nclass is rolled back.\\n\\n```mermaid\\nflowchart TD\\n    Pick[next_uncovered_class<br/>excluding exhausted_classes] --> HasClass{class found?}\\n    HasClass -- no --> WrapUp[Wrap up phase: see section 6.5]\\n    HasClass -- yes --> Snap[Snapshot class_checkpoint = HEAD]\\n    Snap --> AttemptLoop[Per-class attempt loop]\\n    AttemptLoop --> CheckAttempts{class_attempts < max-iterations?}\\n    CheckAttempts -- no --> Exhaust[Mark class exhausted<br/>commit if any partial gain]\\n    Exhaust --> ClearCtx\\n    CheckAttempts -- yes --> Render[Render class-targeted prompt:<br/>active class, source file,<br/>uncovered call sites, progress delta]\\n    Render --> Send[agent.send_prompt]\\n    Send --> TestLoop[Test retry loop]\\n\\n    TestLoop --> RunTest[run_test_command<br/>'./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=...']\\n    RunTest --> Failed{first failed task}\\n    Failed -- \\\"nativeTest or none\\\" --> ReachedNT[reached_native_test = true]\\n    Failed -- \\\"earlier task\\\" --> SendErr[Send failing output back to agent]\\n    SendErr --> CheckTestBudget{test attempts<br/>< max-class-test-iterations?}\\n    CheckTestBudget -- yes --> RunTest\\n    CheckTestBudget -- no --> Rollback[git reset --hard class_checkpoint<br/>class_failed = true]\\n    Rollback --> ClearCtx\\n\\n    ReachedNT --> RegenReport[generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport]\\n    RegenReport --> ReportOK{report loaded?}\\n    ReportOK -- no --> HardFail([Return RUN_STATUS_FAILURE])\\n    ReportOK -- yes --> Delta[compute_class_delta<br/>previous vs current report]\\n    Delta --> ClassState{class state}\\n    ClassState -- \\\"uncovered_calls == 0\\\" --> Resolved[Commit test sources<br/>successful_classes += 1<br/>add to exhausted_classes]\\n    Resolved --> ResolvedGate[Native test verification gate<br/>see section 6.4]\\n    ResolvedGate --> ResolvedGateOK{gate result}\\n    ResolvedGateOK -- PASSED --> ClearCtx\\n    ResolvedGateOK -- FAILED --> HardFail\\n    ClassState -- \\\"covered_calls increased\\\" --> PartialCommit[Commit partial coverage<br/>advance class_checkpoint]\\n    PartialCommit --> PartialGate[Native test verification gate<br/>see section 6.4]\\n    PartialGate --> PartialGateOK{gate result}\\n    PartialGateOK -- PASSED --> AttemptLoop\\n    PartialGateOK -- FAILED --> HardFail\\n    ClassState -- \\\"no gain\\\" --> AttemptLoop\\n    ClassState -- \\\"class disappeared\\\" --> Disappear{covered_calls increased<br/>overall?}\\n    Disappear -- yes --> Resolved\\n    Disappear -- no --> Skip[Skip class, mark exhausted]\\n    Skip --> ClearCtx\\n\\n    ClearCtx[agent.clear_context] --> Pick\\n```\\n\\nNotes on the inner test-retry loop:\\n\\n- \\\"First failed task\\\" is computed by parsing Gradle's failure summary. Tasks\\n  before `nativeTest` (typically `compileTestJava`, `test`, etc.) signal that\\n  the new code is broken and the agent receives the failing output. Reaching\\n  `nativeTest` is treated as success for this stage even if `nativeTest`\\n  itself fails — coverage data is the deciding signal.\\n- If the test retry budget is exhausted without ever reaching `nativeTest`,\\n  the class is rolled back to `class_checkpoint`, preserving prior committed\\n  classes.\\n\\n### 6.3 Coverage report mid-run failure\\n\\nA missing or unparsable `dynamic-access-coverage.json` after the initial\\nphase is a hard failure: the strategy returns `RUN_STATUS_FAILURE` with the\\nprompt-iteration count, and the entry script resets the branch to\\n`checkpoint_commit_hash`.\\n\\n### 6.4 Per-class native-test verification gate\\n\\nAfter every per-class iteration that committed a coverage gain — i.e. the\\n**Resolved** or **PartialCommit** branches in §6.2 — the strategy queues\\none native-test verification step. When the queue reaches\\n`native-test-verification-batch-size` (default `5`), the strategy invokes\\nthe [Native test verification gate](native-test-verification.md) for the\\ncurrent coordinate with\\n\\n```text\\noutput_dir = tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/build/natively-collected/<class-key>/\\n```\\n\\nwhere `<class-key>` is a sanitized form of the class name the per-class\\niteration that triggered the batch flush just resolved or advanced, with a\\nbatch suffix when the flush contains more than one class step. If the loop\\nfinishes, or a large-library chunk boundary is reached, with fewer than the\\nconfigured number of queued class steps, the strategy flushes that partial\\nbatch before returning. The gate always starts with the normal JVM-agent\\nmetadata path, but writes that output to a per-gate staging directory:\\n\\n```text\\n./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=<g:a:v> --agentAllowedPackages=fromJar --metadataOutputDir=<output_dir>/agent\\n./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=<g:a:v> -PmetadataConfigDirs=<output_dir>/agent\\n```\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_40\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '300,380p' docs/DEVELOPING.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_40\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '300,380p' docs/DEVELOPING.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"```\\n\\n### Quick reference (copy/paste)\\n\\n- Style: `./gradlew checkstyle`\\n- Format check: `./gradlew spotlessCheck`\\n- Format apply: `./gradlew spotlessApply`\\n- Pull images (single lib): `./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`\\n- Check metadata (single lib): `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`\\n- Generate metadata (single lib): `./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=group:artifact:version`\\n- Build trace-enabled native image: `./gradlew nativeTraceImage -Pcoordinates=group:artifact:version`\\n- Run trace-enabled native image: `./gradlew runNativeTraceImage -Pcoordinates=group:artifact:version -PtraceMetadataPath=<absolute-trace-output-dir> -PtraceMetadataConditionPackages=<package1,package2,...>`\\n- Merge native trace metadata: `./gradlew mergeNativeTraceMetadata -PinputDirs=<absolute-trace-output-dir-0>,<absolute-trace-output-dir-1>,... -PoutputDir=<absolute-merged-metadata-dir>`\\n- Split test-only metadata: `./gradlew splitTestOnlyMetadata -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|group:artifact|k/n|all]`\\n- Fix test that fails Native Image run for new library version: `./gradlew fixTestNativeImageRun -PtestLibraryCoordinates=group:artifact:version -PnewLibraryVersion=version`\\n- Test (single lib): `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`\\n- List resolved tested-library jars: `./gradlew listLibraryJars -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`\\n- Generate dynamic access report: `./gradlew generateDynamicAccessReport -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`\\n- Generate dynamic access coverage report: `./gradlew generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`\\n  Output: `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/test/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\\n  JSON top-level fields: `coordinate`, `hasDynamicAccess`, `totals`, `classes`\\n- Coverage (single lib): `./gradlew jacocoTestReport -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`\\n- Generate library stats: `./gradlew generateLibraryStats -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|group:artifact|k/n|all]`\\n- Validate library stats: `./gradlew validateLibraryStats`\\n- List available coordinates: `./gradlew listCoordinates -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|group:artifact|k/n|all] [-PstrictCoordinates=true]`\\n- Generate dependency graph: `./gradlew generateDependencyGraph -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|group:artifact|k/n|all]`\\n- Analyze external dynamic access: `./gradlew analyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccess --coordinates=group:artifact:version`\\n- Scan changed Docker images: `./gradlew checkAllowedDockerImages --baseCommit=<sha1> --newCommit=<sha2>`\\n- Scan all Docker images: `./gradlew checkAllowedDockerImages`\\n- List libs with newer versions: `./gradlew fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions --quiet`\\n- Record a newly tested version: `./gradlew addTestedVersion -Pcoordinates=\\\"group:artifact:newVersion\\\" --lastSupportedVersion=\\\"oldVersion\\\"`\\n- Package release artifacts: `./gradlew package`\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_41\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"I found the repo’s dynamic-access tooling, which is better aligned with this task than guessing from the green smoke test. I’m generating the per-callsite coverage report for `caffeine:2.9.3` under the pinned GraalVM so I can target the actual uncovered reflection paths.\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_42\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc 'env GRAALVM_HOME=/home/vjovanov/c/graalvm-reachability-metadata/vj/forge/ce/sdk/latest_graalvm_home JAVA_HOME=/home/vjovanov/c/graalvm-reachability-metadata/vj/forge/ce/sdk/latest_graalvm_home PATH=/home/vjovanov/c/graalvm-reachability-metadata/vj/forge/ce/sdk/latest_graalvm_ho