r and field registrations are actually required for untested cache variants.\nThe repo’s own coverage data is the first concrete signal: `stats/com.github.ben-manes.caffeine/caffeine/2.9.3/stats.json` shows only `14/21` reflection calls covered for this version. I’m using that to drive a more complete fix rather than treating the current green test run as sufficient.\nI found the repo’s dynamic-access tooling, which is better aligned with this task than guessing from the green smoke test. I’m generating the per-callsite coverage report for `caffeine:2.9.3` under the pinned GraalVM so I can target the actual uncovered reflection paths.\nThe dynamic-access report narrowed it down cleanly: the only uncovered reflection paths are in `com.github.benmanes.caffeine.base.UnsafeAccess` and `com.github.benmanes.caffeine.cache.UnsafeAccess`. I’m inspecting those source files next so I can register the exact fields and helper classes they lazily resolve.\nI found persisted test-run artifacts for this exact coordinate under `build/tests/...`. I’m checking those logs now in case one of them captured the original missing-registration failure that the current clean run no longer reproduces.\nI’m moving from symptom-checking to a broader compatibility fix. The plan is to validate which of the newer Caffeine metadata entries also exist in `2.9.3`, then backport only the entries that match the `2.9.3` class layout and constructor signatures.\nI have a concrete missing path now: `weakKeys()` with strong values resolves `WS` and `FS`, and `2.9.3` has no metadata for that constructor/factory pair. I’m adding a focused weak-keys-only test first so the gap reproduces in the repo test suite before I patch the metadata.\nThe missing-registration failure is now reproduced concretely: `Class.forName(\"com.github.benmanes.caffeine.cache.WS\")` fails in `LocalCacheFactory.newBoundedLocalCache`. I’m patching the `WS` constructor metadata and its `FS` node metadata together, since `weakKeys()` needs both sides of that path.\nThe weak-keys-only path now passes in native mode with the patched metadata. I’m doing the final verification sweep under the same GraalVM: rechecking `native-image --version`, validating the metadata file, and regenerating the dynamic-access coverage report to confirm the new path is exercised.\nUpdated Caffeine `2.9.3` for the missing weak-keys metadata path. In [reachability-metadata.json](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/6833-eee193e9/metadata/com.github.ben-manes.caffeine/caffeine/2.9.3/reachability-metadata.json:115) and [reachability-metadata.json](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/6833-eee193e9/metadata/com.github.ben-manes.caffeine/caffeine/2.9.3/reachability-metadata.json:529) I added metadata for the `FS` node fields/constructor and the `WS` bounded cache constructor. In [EvictionTest.java](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/6833-eee193e9/tests/src/com.github.ben-manes.caffeine/caffeine/2.9.3/src/test/java/com_github_ben_manes_caffeine/caffeine/EvictionTest.java:56) I added a `weakKeys()` strong-value case to reproduce and guard the fix.\n\nVerification used the required GraalVM only. `native-image --version` matched the requested `25.0.2 / Oracle GraalVM 25.1.0-dev+10.1`, and these commands passed:\n`./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.github.ben-manes.caffeine:caffeine:2.9.3 --stacktrace`\n`./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=com.github.ben-manes.caffeine:caffeine:2.9.3 --stacktrace`\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
